{"type":"message","id":"9f47408a","parentId":"207eb37b","timestamp":"2026-02-18T18:12:03.667Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-02-18 20:12 GMT+2] OPERATION: IRON CORE (RUST COMPILATION).\n\n1.  **Environment Check:**\n    *   `cargo --version` confirmed: 1.93.1.\n    *   `rustc --version` confirmed: 1.93.1.\n\n2.  **Rust Compilation (`src/rust_core`):**\n    *   *Navigate:* `cd src/rust_core`.\n    *   *Build:* `cargo build --release`.\n    *   *Target:* Look for `target/release/dmarket_rust_core.dll` (Windows) or `.so` (Linux).\n\n3.  **Python Integration (PyO3 Binding):**\n    *   *Setup:* Ensure `Cargo.toml` has `crate-type = [\"cdylib\"]`.\n    *   *Rename:* Copy `.dll` to `.pyd` so Python can import it directly.\n    *   *Link:* Edit `src/dmarket/api/client.py` to `import dmarket_rust_core`.\n\n4.  **Benchmark (The Proof):**\n    *   Run `python tests/perf/rust_vs_python.py` again.\n    *   *Goal:* Rust latency < 0.01 ms (CPU time).\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Build status.\n    *   Path to binary.\n    *   Latency comparison."}],"timestamp":1771438323665}}
